<div style="padding-left: 20px; font-size: x-large">
<h1>Step 01 - Install Tailwind</h1>
<ul>
    <li>There are a lot of resources on the internet on how to integrate Tailwind with Blazor, most require npm<br/><br/></li>
    <li>To use tailwind without requiring npm we prefer an approach similar to: <a href="https://github.com/tesar-tech/BlazorAndTailwind">https://github.com/tesar-tech/BlazorAndTailwind</a></li>
    <li>Just download the latest release from <a href="https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/releases">https://github.com/tailwindlabs/tailwindcss/releases</a></li>
    <li>Copy tailwindcss-windows-x64.exe to the Client project</li>
    <li>Rename it to tw.exe<br/><br/></li>
    <li>
        Add a new file tailwind.config.js to the Client project with these contents:
        <pre>
module.exports = {
    content: [
        './**/*.html',
        './**/*.razor',
    ],
    theme: {
        extend: {
        },
    },
    plugins: [],
}
</pre>
        This will scan all .html and .razor files in our project for tailwind classes to be generated into the minified css.<br/><br/>
    </li>
    <li>
        Add a custom tailwind.css file to the Client project with these contents:
        <pre>@@tailwind base;
@@tailwind components;
@@tailwind utilities;
        </pre>
        This defines the base of css classes generated by tailwind.<br/><br/>
    </li>
    <li>
        Create a batch file 'tailwindwatch.bat' with these contents:
        <pre>tw -i ./tailwind.css -o ./wwwroot/css/tailwind.min.css --watch</pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        Run the tailwindwatch.bat in a cmd window, it converts the tailwind.css into a tailwind.min.css that is not yet used by the application (see next step)
    </li>
    <li>Run application using the watch.bat (in the Server project), it should show this page with default html styling<br/><br/></li>
    <li>Go to next page: <a href="/step02">Next</a></li>
</ul>
</div>
